        "name": "Steve Guminski",
        "email": "stephenx.guminski@intel.com",
        "username": "sguminsx",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-08-22 17:42:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI've updated the liblustreapi_cmd variable to be local only.  I've also moved the calls to set/clear the command name so that they surround the calls to Parser_execarg().  This allows the utility and command name to be displayed without requiring the calls to be made in each individual handler.  However, this only occurs in non-interactive mode.\n\nSetting the command name in interactive mode would require changing the Parser_commands() function, and would cause a dependency between libcfs and liblustreapi.  Since the user presumably know which command they just typed, is it acceptable that interactive mode prints only the utility name?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
